[ starter maintenance ]
- 30g     / 18g filtered water
- 50g     / 30g flour
- 20-25g  / 12g starter

[ mixing ]
- combine in a bowl:
  - 500g bread flour
  - 350g water (70%) (for 80:20 white:wholemeal bread flour)
  - 50g active stiff starter (10%)
  - 10g salt
- wait 30 mins
- do windowpane translucency test
  - if it tears, knead 2-3 mins, rest 10 mins, repeat

[ fermentation ]
- with wet hands, round the dough to make nice round surface
- cover bowl and let dough rise, 6-12 hrs, but go based on criteria:
  - 30% - 50% volume rise (use aliquot jar)
  - surface bubbles visible
  - jiggly texture when bowl shaken
  - sweet/sour smell
- optionally stretch and fold during fermentation

[ shaping ]
- use batard (oval) or boulard (round)
- sprinkle some flour over dough while still in bowl
  - flip dough from bowl onto bench (i.e. topside in bowl -> bottomside on bench)
    - this is because topside in bowl is slightly drier
  - add some flour around edges of dough
  - fold (sticky) now-topside over a few times, knocking excess flour off
    - right to middle
    - left to middle
    - top to middle
  - roll top to middle to yield a smooth topside
  - add some flour on top 
  - flip into banneton

[ prooving ]
- cover and refrigerate 8-96 hours to proof, or proof at room temp for 1-3 hours
- set oven to 230°C with dutch oven inside and preheat for 30 mins
- score & spritz loaf, optionally add rice flour
- bake 30 mins with dutch oven lid on
- bake until desired crust colour / until internal temp reaches 92°C (20 more mins) with lid off

